com.here.platform.location.core.mapmatching.javadsl

Interface Interpolator<O,V,T>


  • public interface Interpolator<O,V,T>

    This is an experimental API. It may be removed or changed from one version to the next.

    An Interpolator inserts MatchResults into the provided MatchedPath.results, one for each observation that was marked as Omitted. It also updates MatchedPath.transitions accordingly. This does not modify the original MatchedPath.

    • If you are interested in positions on the path for the interpolated results, use a projecting interpolator, which creates OnRoad results. The matchedPath must contain transitions for a projecting interpolator to work. To create a projecting interpolator, use the factory method Interpolators.projecting.
    • If you are not interested in interpolated positions, use a ToUnknown interpolator. It inserts an Unknown for each observation that was marked a Omitted. To create a ToUnknown interpolator, use the factory method Interpolators.filteredToUnknown.

    See also PathMatcherWithFilter for more information about filtering and interpolation.
